  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 4 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 16 high, 6 medium, 17 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Timişoara Traian Vuia (TSR/LRTR); plus 13 other bases. 6 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI). Network hotspots: Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Castellón-Costa Azahar (CDT/LECH), Lisbon Humberto Delgado (LIS/LPPT), Almaty (ALA/UAAA). Primary drivers: approach minima limits, very low visibility and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Castellón-Costa Azahar (CDT/LECH), Lisbon Humberto Delgado (LIS/LPPT) and 9 others.",
